This paper is about a toolkit for text generation, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also emphasizes the modularity, versatility, and extensibility of the toolkit, which suggests that it may be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions large-scale pretrained models, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
